The paper discusses neural models for representation learning and reasoning, which are typically studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The specific model being studied, the Neural Theorem Prover (NTP), involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and neural networks (cs.NE).
